<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,151,467]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,370,395]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang et al. (2010)" authorityName="Zhang et al." authorityYear="2010" box="[583,957,370,395]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Taperus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bannaensis">
<emphasis box="[583,736,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">T. bannaensis</emphasis>
Zhang 
<emphasis box="[820,869,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</taxonomicName>
in coloration but differs in the shape of the aedeagus and male pygofer. In the latter the male pygofer is more conical posteriorly and elongate compared to more rounded and shorter pygofer in 
<taxonomicName box="[569,675,442,467]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Taperus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indicus">
<emphasis box="[569,675,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">T. indicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
